Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Developer position with Penguin Random House. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web development with React, JavaScript, Java, Python, and SQL, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and developed modern web applications using React and JavaScript, building both front-end and backend components to serve internal and external users across the platform. I built RESTful APIs and backend services in Python with SQL database integration (PostgreSQL), translating business requirements into scalable solutions that support thousands of customer workflows — giving me direct experience working across the full stack. To keep these systems production-ready, I leveraged AWS cloud services (Lambda, API Gateway, S3, CloudWatch) and DevOps practices to deploy, monitor, and iterate on technology products with continuous improvement and automation. I also implemented accessibility and security best practices across web applications, ensuring compliance with modern web standards and protecting user data — both critical to building products that serve diverse audiences. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to full-stack development of an Identity & Access Management platform using React, Spring Boot (Java), and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications in an agile development environment. I also built a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, SQL (PostgreSQL), and Redis that handles file operations across AWS S3 and Google Cloud Storage, and developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions and Lambda to handle long-running data imports — both of which required the kind of systems-level thinking and operational stability focus this role demands. Importantly, I supported legacy systems while driving platform evolution toward modern architectures in a fast-paced development environment, which aligns directly with Penguin Random House's need to support legacy systems and transition them to modern architectures. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to the design, development, and maintenance of modern web applications as part of your ongoing platform evolution.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in technical problem-solving and communication — skills that translate directly into the collaborative culture and communication responsibilities this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I developed Python machine learning pipelines using PyTorch on HPC infrastructure, demonstrating backend development skills with complex technical systems. I also deployed models using cloud services and DevOps workflows, ensuring secure and efficient AI application serving. Beyond building the systems myself, I communicated technical concepts clearly to technical and non-technical stakeholders through workshops for 50+ students — directly mirroring the communication skills valued in this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to Penguin Random House and its mission.

I have always been passionate about creating books for everyone and celebrating diversity through technology, and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of igniting a universal passion for reading by creating books for everyone. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

